messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
I think we're on I-75.
I-75? Do you know what mile marker?
No, I can't see anything. The fog is so dense and we just hit a guardrail. I think there was an accident behind us because I heard it.
Are you northbound or southbound?
We are going southbound on I-75.
Okay, we're going to get you some help out there. What's the phone number you're calling from?
Oh my gosh, it's so dark here.
Okay, and what is the city that you're nearest? Have you seen any signs for a city recently?
Are we near Gainesville? We just passed Gainesville, University.
Okay, hold on just one second while I get this in, okay?
Okay, it's very dangerous, so please be careful.
Are you out of the roadway?
We are out as far as we possibly can.
That's good. Are there any injuries in your vehicle?
No, no, thank God.
But I think I heard another crash back there.
You heard another crash?
I thought I did, but I'm not sure.
What's the color, make, and model of your vehicle?
We just hit the guardrail.
Did you hit the guardrail or was there another vehicle involved?
No, we hit the guardrail.
Okay, and you said you are out of the road as much as you can be? Are you blocking any lanes?
No.
Oh, someone stopped to help us.
That's good, but stay inside your vehicle until law enforcement gets there. Do you smell any gas or see any leaks?
No, just the smoke from the fog.
Okay, hold on just one second. We are getting help out there to you. Are you able to talk to my friend?
Yes, sure.
Hello, ma'am. We have help on the way. I'm showing you near Mile Marker 379, could that be right?
Yeah, we passed the exit to Gainesville, right?
Are you southbound?
Yes, ma'am.
Okay, just wanted to double check. What's your name?
No injuries, but I think we need a tow truck.
That's fine. We can sort that out. I'm going to stay on the line with you until units find you. It's very hazy, so I want to make sure they can locate you.
It's really bad out here. People are stopping.
If you're going southbound, are you on the left side or the right side of the road?
I pulled the car all the way to the right side onto the grass.
Okay, you said the right side?
Hold on just one second. Okay.
Oh no, another accident!
There was another accident?
Yes, a truck. I think it was a semi.
What kind of truck, like a semi or a pickup?
We can't see. The haze is too thick.
I do hear a police officer or an ambulance.
Hold on just one second. Stand on the line, don't hang up.
No problem.
Okay, you said another vehicle hit northbound?
Yes, it looks like another accident on the other side.
This is the third one now.
All right, if you're able to, turn on your emergency flashers, get out of your vehicle, and move as far away from traffic as possible.
Okay, we're out as far as we can be.
You're doing really well. Are there any obvious injuries in any other vehicles that you can see?
No, but it's hard to see anything.
Okay, just tell everyone to turn on their headlights and flashers and get out of the road.
Okay, she said everyone get as far off the road as you can and put on your flashers.
Is everyone out of their vehicles?
Yes, ma'am.
I'm going to ask you some medical questions. How many people would you guess are injured?
Oh no, another accident!
Okay, that's the fourth vehicle now. Are you with the patients right now?
No, we are too far away. We can't see much.
Do you know if there are chemicals or other hazards involved?
Couldn't tell you.
Another crash!
This is bad, people can't see. Is anyone pinned or trapped in their vehicles?
We can't tell. This is getting worse. Another one just happened.
Okay, how many vehicles now?
16 now.
Okay, do you see any fire or anything like that?
No fire. We can hardly see our hazards.
Here comes another one. Oh my God, they're coming too fast!
Just keep yourself out of traffic. Try to direct people out of the road if you can, but keep safe.
Paramedics and police are on the way. Lots of help is coming.
Another accident! This is getting bad.
Just keep your hazard lights on and stay out of traffic. Help is on the way.
Don't offer anyone anything to eat or drink, it might make them sick.
Let anyone injured rest in the most comfortable position. Don't move them unless it's absolutely necessary.
We see some people lying on the floor. There's someone with a flashlight now.
You're doing a great job. Just keep everyone calm and wait for help. Are the semis rolled over?
We can't see very well.
There's people crying. I think someone might be dying.
Can you see anything specific or just hear crying?
We're seeing some lights now from other vehicles.
Okay, please hold on and stay on the line.
Should I give you another number in case my phone dies?
Yes, please give me the other number.
